 To appoint such employees, agents, and representatives as it may
deem necessary, and to determine the compensation and to define the
duties of each;

 To keep minutes, books, and records which will reflect all of the
acts and transactions of the committee and which shall be subject to
examination by the Secretary;

 To prepare periodic statements of the financial operations of the
committee and to make copies of each such statement available to
growers and handlers for examination at the office of the committee;

 To cause its books to be audited by a certified public accountant
at least once each fiscal year, and at such other times as the
Secretary may request;

 To engage in such research relating to the determination of
maturity and grade standards for avocados as may be approved by the
Secretary;

 To notify, as provided in this part, producers and handlers of all
meetings of the committee to consider recommendations for
regulation;

 A complete record of the quantities disposed of by him, segregated
as to varieties and as to the respective quantities subject to
regulation and not subject to regulation;

 Location (by county, highway, rural route, distance from nearest
town, etc.) of grove from which avocados are to be shipped pursuant
to the requested exemption certificate;

 Information as to the average size of such avocados and the reasons
why applicant believes he is entitled to an exemption certificate;
and

 Place within production area where the avocados will be prepared
for market, and name and address of person responsible for such
preparation;
